</ul>

<p>Now I wish this <a href="http://hsivonen.iki.fi/online-photos/">process was a little better.</a></p>

<p>If the Wikipedia contributor didn&#8217;t mail me, how would I know he used my pictures?</p>

<a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/hendry/189880411/" title="Photo Sharing"><img src="http://static.flickr.com/73/189880411_9bb12a1977_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="Early Iron age dagger" /></a>

<p>I don&#8217;t consider Flickr to be my central image store and I have <a href="http://pictures.natalian.org/">tons of pictures</a> that are public domain in <a href="http://trac.natalian.org/browser/projects/pik">my own image gallery system.</a></p>

<p>I wonder <strong>how I should license/tag/meta my pictures</strong> so that search engines (Google) know they&#8217;re in the public domain and people can find them.</p>